aVBut doctors can't make sure your wishes are respected
p228
aVuntil they know what they are.
p229
aa(lp230
VWould you want to be on life support if it offered any chance of longer life?
p231
aVAre you most worried about the quality of that time,
p232
aVrather than quantity?
p233
aVBoth of those choices are thoughtful and brave,
p234
aVbut for all of us, it's our choice.
p235
aVThat's true at the end of life
p236
aVand for medical care throughout our lives.
p237
aVIf you're pregnant, do you want genetic screening?
p238
aVIs a knee replacement right or not?
p239
aVDo you want to do dialysis in a clinic or at home?
p240
aVThe answer is:
p241
aVit depends.
p242
aVWhat medical care will help you live the way you want to?
p243
aVI hope you remember that question
p244
aVthe next time you face a decision in your health care.
p245
aVRemember that you always have a choice,
p246
aVand it is OK to say no to a treatment that's not right for you.
