aa(lp258
VWhen Paul said, "It's going to be OK,"
p259
aVthat didn't mean that we could cure his illness.
p260
aVInstead, we learned to accept both joy and sadness at the same time;
p261
aVto uncover beauty and purpose
p262
aVboth despite and because we are all born
p263
aVand we all die.
p264
aVAnd for all the sadness and sleepless nights,
p265
aVit turns out there is joy.
